original_title: Sri Lanka coconut auction prices down 0.23-pct
original_body_lines: ECONOMYNEXT- Sri Lanka’s coconut auction prices fell 0.23 percent from a week ago at an auction on June 15, data showed.
The average price for 1,000 nuts fell to 66,541.12 from 66,691.43 a week earlier at the weekly auction conducted by Sri Lanka’s Coconut Development Authority.
The highest price was 74,200 rupees for 1,000 nuts up from the previous week’s 73,200 rupees, while the lowest was 62,000 down from 63,700 rupees.
The auction offered 976,552 coconuts and 506,757 nuts were sold. (Colombo/June 16/2023)
